action.content:
You are an applicant in a job interview. Here is a description of your CV:

WHAT: Job Application
BACHELOR: Chemistry
INDUSTRY-EXPERIENCE: Three years
HIGHEST-EDUCATION: PostDoc
OTHER-SKILLS: Research
AVAILABILITY: In two weeks

The recruiter does not know about it yet. 

Questions from the recruiter will start with RECRUITER. Please reply in the form: ANSWER: <some text>

I will also ask you questions. These questions will start with ME: . Please answer these questions with: ASIDE: <some text>

Important: Give short, direct answers!

Let us start.
Begin probing
ME:  Does the interviewer know what your bachelor's degree is? Please answer yes or no.
ASIDE: The interviewer does not know my bachelor's degree yet.
NA

ASIDE: The interviewer does not know my bachelor's degree yet, as it has not been explicitly mentioned in the provided information.
NA

ASIDE: No, the interviewer does not know about my bachelor's degree yet.
no

Answer is correct.

no

ASIDE: No, I have not informed the interviewer about my other skills yet.
no
Answer for OTHER-SKILLS valid after 1 tries.
Answer is correct.
ME:  Does the recruiter know when you can start? Please answer yes or no.
ASIDE: The recruiter does not know yet. I will inform them that I am available to start in two weeks.
NA
ME: Please answer this question carefully. Does the recruiter know when you can start? Please answer yes or no.
ASIDE: The recruiter does not know yet when I can start.
NA
ME: Please follow my instructions. Does the recruiter know when you can start? Please answer yes or no.
ANSWTER: No
NA
ME: Please be specific now. Does the recruiter know when you can start? Please answer yes or no.
ASIDE: No, the recruiter does not know when I can start.
no
Answer for AVAILABILITY valid after 4 tries.
Answer is correct.
End probing
What is the next request?
When would you be able to start working here?
RECRUITER: When would you be able to start working here?
I would be able to start working here in two weeks.
